CAPE TOWN - Flash floods have caused chaos in parts of Cape Town. People have been urged to drive carefully as heavy rains continue to fall in the city. READ: Cape Town roads flooded after heavy downpours Informal settlements in areas including Khayelitsha, Lwandle, Macassar and Kalkfontein have been affected. Assessments are under way and humanitarian relief has been requested. The much-needed rain comes as the city continues to suffer from a devastating drought. eNCA